Puzzling over the levels of media interest in two maritime disasters is a very odd question for the #Guardian to pose. The sinking of a #refugee trawler in the Mediterranean is one of a very large set of identical tragedies. The other is practically unique. If billionnaires were lost on dangerous expeditions at the same rate as refugees, they wouldn't be "newsworthy," and for a newspaper to feign otherwise is a bit rum.

content:
did some testing with @luna@f.l4.pm on the upcoming cpu/gpu clock increase on #quest2 in #vrchat specifically, comparing OS v54 (current stable) vs v55 (upcoming, currently available in public test channel)

default vrc home world, looking in mirror (probably gpu capped): 52fps vs 58fps
my music visualizer world (cpu capped): 45fps vs 47fps
my music visualizer world (added gpu load, should be gpu capped): 34fps vs 42fps

overall, good improvement.

we also noticed boot time has decreased (not in this update, but a prior one) - currently on both v54 and v55 it's 16 seconds from display illuminated to rendering something other than the boot logo i.e. guardian or quest home, compared to 30+ seconds on prior versions
